	     Johannesburg – Grass-cutters discovered a baby's body in a plastic shopping bag near the Tsakane Mall, Ekurhuleni, on Tuesday morning, Gauteng police said. In a statement, Tsakane police spokesperson Lerato Mngomezulu said the plastic bag with the body was found next to a storm drain. The gender of the baby is unknown. Mngomezulu appealed to the public to assist in finding the mother of the infant. Anyone with suspicion of who the suspect could be should contact the Tsakane Police on (011) 363-5300.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  